Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportLengthViolation(25.10)                      reportLengthViolation(25.10)

Name
       reportLengthViolation  - Runs timing analysis and reports nets that ex-
       ceed the maximum length constraint set  by  setOptMode  -opt_max_length
       parameter

Syntax
       reportLengthViolation

       [-help]

       [-all | -noGlobalNets]

       [-selNetFile <selNetFileName>]

       [-excNetFile <excNetFileName>]

       [-histogram]

       [-outfile <fileName>]

       [-significant_digits <integer>]

       Runs  timing  analysis  and reports nets that exceed the maximum length
       constraint set by setOptMode -opt_max_length parameter.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportLengthViolation parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportLengthViolation

       -all   Reports violations on all nets.

       -noGlobalNets
              Reports violations on all nets except  for  power,  ground,  and
              clock nets.

              Note: The parameters, -all and -noGlobalNets are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -excNetFile <excNetFileName>
              Specifies  a file that lists the names of hierarchical nets that
              are to be excluded from the report.

       -outfile <fileName>
              Specifies the report file name.

       -selNetFile <selNetFileName>
              Specifies a file that lists the names of  hierarchical  nets  to
              consider  in  the  report. Only violations on the nets listed in
              the file are considered in the report.

              Note: The parameters, -selNetFile and -excNetFile are not  mutu-
              ally  exclusive.  If both parameters are specified, the -excNet-
              File parameter overides the -selNetFile parameter.

       -histogram
              Generates a histogram in addition to the default reporting.

       -significant_digits <integer>
              Allows you to specify the number of significant digits.

              Default: 3

